{{Infobox person | image = | name = Bobby Mair | birth_name = | birth_date = 1986{{cn|date=January 2018}} | birth_place = [[Toronto]],{{cn|date=January 2018}} Ontario, Canada | occupation = [[Comedian]] | spouse = Harriet Kemsley | website = }} '''Bobby Mair''' is a Canadian stand-up comedian based in London, England who has appeared on ''[[The Hour (Canadian TV series)|The Hour]]'', ''[[Russell Howard's Good News]]'', ''[[Sweat the Small Stuff]]'', ''[[Virtually Famous]]'', ''[[Never Mind the Buzzcocks]]'', ''[[Sam Delaney's News Thing]]'' and ''[[8 Out of 10 Cats]]''. Mair won the Laughing Horse New Act Of The Year competition in 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.chortle.co.uk/comics/b/33861/bobby_mair |title=Bobby Mair, comedian : Chortle : The UK Comedy Guide |first= |last= |work=chortle.co.uk |year=2014 |quote=won the Laughing Horse New Act Of The Year competition in 2012. |accessdate=13 March 2014}}</ref> He has supported the likes of [[Jerry Sadowitz]], [[Doug Stanhope]] and [[Bill Burr]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chortle.co.uk/shows/edinburgh_fringe_2012/m/20882/michelle_de_swarte_&_bobby_mair:_unbalanced|title=Michelle de Swarte & Bobby Mair: Unbalanced : Chortle : The UK Comedy Guide|first=Powder Blue Internet Business|last=Solutions|website=www.chortle.co.uk}}</ref>
== Personal life == Mair was adopted.<ref name=RB/> He is married to comedienne Harriet Kemsley.<ref name=RB>''[[Roast Battle]]'' e3, 17 January 2018</ref> The build-up to the wedding was documented on [[Viceland]] show ''Bobby and Harriet Get Married''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2017-08-02/bobby-and-harriet-get-married-a-wry-fresh-take-on-the-dysfunctional-relationship-comedy/|title=Bobby and Harriet Get Married: a wry, fresh take on the dysfunctional relationship comedy|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.comedy.co.uk/tv/bobby_and_harriet_get_married/|title=Bobby And Harriet Get Married - VICELAND Comedy - British Comedy Guide|first=British Comedy|last=Guide|website=British Comedy Guide}}</ref>
He is a third cousin of Canadian pop star [[Justin Bieber]] - although he says that they have never met - a fact mentioned many times, including in his Edinburgh Fringe show ''obviously adopted''.<ref name="Obviously Adopted">{{cite web|url=http://www.comedy.co.uk/fringe/2013/bobby_mair/|title=Bobby Mair - Edinburgh Fringe 2013 - British Comedy Guide|first=British Comedy|last=Guide|website=British Comedy Guide}}</ref>
